Messier catalog data (messier.json) is derived from well-known public-domain
astronomical data. Positions and magnitudes are J2000 epoch coordinates compiled
from standard references including the original Messier catalog and subsequent
corrections. The Messier catalog is in the public domain.

Constellation name translations (data/constellation-names/*.json) are
hand-curated translations of the 88 IAU constellation names into English,
Chinese, Arabic, and Modern Greek. The IAU constellation names themselves
are standard nomenclature in the public domain; translations were compiled
from standard references (interlanguage Wikipedia entries and the
corresponding national-language astronomical literature) and are released
as part of this project under the Apache 2.0 license.

